<br>
When I was an Axe skald, I used Evernight/Arctic Rift, Havoc, Plague and Cleave (been a while... it's the parry reactionary).<br>
<br>
I think it's all the same for any weapon line for the Skald, in that we either use a positional and then throw in the anytime as a backup.<br>
<br>
Reactionary - parry, which is measly but our only defense.. dont bother with evade or block chain.<br>
<br>
What the Skald needs, IMHO, is a weapon line unique to the class. Introduce styles which works off shouts with it's own unique chain that perhaps proc a Body debuff. Or give good positional styles with some effective damage or effect at the LOWER TIER of the weapon line.<br>
<br>
I hope they rework styles in that each has it's own branch of speciality for players to choose from. Be it axe or sword or whatever, there can be like maybe 3 choices to go:<br>
<br>
Reactionary - those who go this route would have access to better styles off evade, parry, block which in turn boosts their own defenses while making their targets more susceptible to attacks.<br>
<br>
Positionals - front, side, rear, medium defense to the user while giving snare, stun or bleed effects to their targets.<br>
<br>
Anytime - high damage attacks altho damaging but are prone to misses, fumbles and procs an effect which hinders the user. It also lowers their defensive ability.<br>
<br>
If they give us this kind of style review... players from various classes can choose how they want to play, not forced into a single role. A skald who wishes to be more defensive, can go by the reactionary route, having styles which boosts his defenses, etc.<br>
<br>
Just some thoughts. Well.... in any case, if the various weapon route is not viable, they shud look into giving each class it's own unique line then.<br>
<br>
~Ghuur (Percival) <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showMessageRange?topicID=762.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=762.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=762.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=762.topic&index=34><img src=http://www.stuckathome.com/skalded/images/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=762.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.threadControl?topicID=762.topic><img src=http://www.stuckathome.com/skalded/images/closethread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=762.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=762.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub36.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowF